<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>

<p>The first generation of meeting bots were fragile. They'd fail to join calls, drop audio streams, and struggle with concurrent sessions. They were built as features, not infrastructure. Meeting Bots 2.0 is different — it's built from the ground up for reliability, scale, and enterprise requirements.</p>

<p>Sonesse is the infrastructure powering this next generation.</p>

<h2 id="reliability">Reliability at Scale</h2>

<p>Guaranteed uptime and performance. Your bots work flawlessly in every meeting — whether you're running one concurrent session or a thousand. Sonesse's infrastructure is designed for the demands of enterprise-scale deployments where downtime isn't an option.</p>

<p>Every component in the pipeline — from meeting join orchestration to media capture and transcription — is built with redundancy and automatic failover. If a node goes down, sessions are seamlessly migrated without any impact on the end user experience.</p>

<h2 id="scaling">Built for Parallel Scale</h2>

<p>Built to handle multiple bots in parallel, seamlessly scaling with your needs. Sonesse's architecture scales horizontally, meaning you can go from 10 concurrent bots to 10,000 without changing a single line of code. The platform automatically provisions capacity based on demand.</p>

<p>This matters because enterprise customers don't have predictable meeting patterns. Monday morning might see 50x the load of Sunday evening. Sonesse handles those spikes automatically.</p>

<h2 id="integration">Easy to Integrate</h2>

<p>Deploy bots across Zoom, Teams, and Google Meet with just a few lines of code. The Universal API abstracts away platform-specific complexity, so your engineering team writes one integration that works everywhere.</p>

<h2 id="security">Enterprise-Grade Security</h2>

<p>Enterprise-grade security ensures user data and communications remain protected at all times. Sonesse provides end-to-end encryption, SOC 2 compliance, and role-based access controls as standard. For organisations with stricter requirements, our on-premise deployment model keeps all data within your own infrastructure.</p>

<h2 id="support">Dedicated Developer Support</h2>

<p>Dedicated developer support to ensure smooth implementation and rapid troubleshooting. Every Sonesse customer gets access to our engineering team for integration support, architecture reviews, and production issue resolution.</p>

<h2 id="pricing">Flexible, Usage-Based Pricing</h2>

<p>Transparent, usage-based pricing that grows with your business, keeping costs predictable. You pay for what you use — no minimum commits, no hidden fees, no surprises. As your meeting bot usage grows, your unit economics improve.</p>

